SIMPLE: tryout
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tryout
<hw>Try"out</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a test of
the performance capability of a person, to ascertain fitness for a
particular task; in sports, a test by which the fitness of a player or
contestant to remain in a certain class is determined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theater)</fld> <def>one or more performances of a
play prior to the official opening, held at a location outside of the
city where it is to be formally presented, conducted for the purpose of
determining audience response or ascertaining weaknesses needing
correction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Try out</ent>⟦br⟧
